channel.title: Very tricky xtele command
channel.description:
i need help
[code]if (command.equals("teleallpk") && playerRights >= 3) { for (Player p : server.playerHandler.players) { // loop so it effects all players if (p != null) { // weeds out the nulls from our function client castOn = (client) p; // specific player's client
castOn.teleportToX = 3316; // replace with your tele X coord castOn.teleportToY = 9376; // replace with your tele Y coord } } }[/code]
this is my error
[code]client.java:7880: cannot find symbol symbol : variable teleportToX location: class client castOn.teleportToX = absX; // replace with your tele X coord
^ client.java:7881: cannot find symbol symbol : variable teleportToY location: class client castOn.teleportToY = absY; // replace with your tele Y coord
^ 2 errors Press any key to continue . . .[/code]

item.title: Very tricky xtele command
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

off-topic:
I remember the days of Project 16, cheezescape, and dodian. When times were simpler. All the variables were the same, yet the servers were much different. Now there’s all these things people are doing. hard coding items into their clients, adding thousands of different half assed tutorials.

Sorry about that, just wish things were the way they were back in those days…

On-Topic: Ya, the variables have changed so much in the “era’s” as i call them. So, you just have to search through your client, and find something close to what we posted. Good Luck.

Read full topic

Ya, qwerty’s right. I believe it is “teleToX” instead of “teleportToX”, and the same goes for the Y

Or maybe toX and toY. I helped someone else with the same problem and those were the variables.
